					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">PPU addresses $2000-23ff represent nametable #0.<br /><br />The last 64 bytes ($23c0-23ff) is called attribute table, and it's complicated, but it tells which parts of the screen (bg) should use which bg palette.<br /><br />Just fill it with zero for now, and the whole screen will use the first palette (bg palette #0 = $3f00-3f03).</div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://nesdoug.com" class="postlink">nesdoug.com</a> -- blog/tutorial on programming for the NES</div>
